    "description": "These changesets extend eps_writer's compatibility with PhasePlots and updates its multiplot capabilities to handle a single PlotWindow or a list of PlotWindows (for example, if you want to plot a slice, projection, off-axis projection, and phase plots in one figure).  Also, the colorbar placement in multiplot routine can now be specified in cb_location as a dict of strings (\"left\", \"right\", \"top\", \"bottom\") with the keys as the fields.  However, this only works if a single PlotWindow is given.\r\n\r\nUpdate 1: using tuples in plot isinstance calls.  Thanks, Kacper!\r\n\r\nUpdate 2: Minor bugfix that I happened to stumble upon when transferring the image to PyX.\r\n\r\nExample code:\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!python\r\n\r\nfrom yt.mods import *\r\nimport yt.visualization.eps_writer as eps\r\n\r\npf = load(\"galaxy0030/galaxy0030\")\r\nslc_fields = [\"Density\", \"Temperature\"]\r\nslc_cmaps = {\"Density\": \"algae\", \"Temperature\": \"hot\"}\r\nplots = []\r\nfor f in slc_fields:\r\n    slc = SlicePlot(pf, 'z', f)\r\n    slc.set_width(25, 'kpc')\r\n    slc.set_cmap(f, slc_cmaps[f])\r\n    plots.append(slc)\r\n\r\nproj = ProjectionPlot(pf, 'z', \"Density\")\r\nproj.set_width(25, \"kpc\")\r\nproj.set_cmap(\"Density\", \"algae\")\r\nplots.append(proj)\r\n\r\nad = pf.h.all_data()\r\nphase = PhasePlot(ad, \"Density\", \"Temperature\", [\"CellMassMsun\"],\r\n                  weight_field=None)\r\nphase.set_cmap(\"CellMassMsun\", \"jet\")\r\nplots.append(phase)\r\n\r\nmp = eps.multiplot_yt(2, 2, plots, bare_axes=False, margins=(0.75,0.75))\r\nmp.save_fig('multi', format='eps')\r\n```",
